        <h2 class="title"><a href="/pew-study-future-internet">PEW study on the future of the internet</a></h2>    <span class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Mon, 2008-12-15 14:51.</span>
    <span class="taxonomy"><ul class="links inline"><li class="first taxonomy_term_5"><a href="/archives/cat_announcements.html" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_5">Announcements</a></li>
<li class="last taxonomy_term_3"><a href="/archives/cat_futurism.html" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_3">Futurism</a></li>
</ul></span>
    <div class="content"><p>PEW Research has released their recent <a href="http://www.pewinternet.org/PPF/r/270/report_display.asp">study on the future of the internet and technology</a> where they interviewed a wide range of technologists and futurists, including yours truly.   It&#8217;s fairly long, and the diverse opinions are perhaps too wide to be synthesized, but there is definitely some interesting stuff in there.</p>
</div>
    <div class="links">&raquo; <ul class="links inline"><li class="first blog_usernames_blog"><a href="/blog/brad" title="Read brad&#039;s latest blog entries." class="blog_usernames_blog">brad&#039;s blog</a></li>
